Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/src/libjasper/heic/heic_dec.c
+++ b/src/libjasper/heic/heic_dec.c
@@ -195,10 +195,18 @@
     /* Get a handle to the primary image. */
-    heif_context_get_primary_image_handle(ctx, &handle);
-
-    int width = heif_image_handle_get_width(handle);
-    int height = heif_image_handle_get_height(handle);
-    JAS_LOGDEBUGF(1, "width %d; height %d\n", width, height);
+    if (heif_context_get_primary_image_handle(ctx, &handle) != 0 || !handle) {
+        jas_logerrorf("heif_context_get_primary_image_handle failed\n");
+        goto error;
+    }
+
+    int width = heif_image_handle_get_width(handle);
+    int height = heif_image_handle_get_height(handle);
+    JAS_LOGDEBUGF(1, "width %d; height %d\n", width, height);
 '}`
responded: The root cause of the null dereference is that `heif_context_get_primary_image_handle(ctx, &handle);` may fail, leaving `handle` as `NULL`. The code then immediately calls `heif_image_handle_get_width(handle);` and `heif_decode_image(handle, ...)` without checking if `handle` is non-NULL, leading to a null pointer dereference.

**Patch Plan:**
- After calling `heif_context_get_primary_image_handle`, check if it succeeded (the function returns 0 on success, nonzero on failure).
- If it fails, log an error and goto error handling.
- Only proceed to use `handle` if it is valid.

